# Get Guide by ID

This endpoint retrieves information about a specific guide by their ID.

## Request

### Request Body
This endpoint does not require a request body.

### Request Parameters
- `ID`: The unique identifier of the guide. 

## Response

### Response Body
The response will be a JSON object with the following properties:
- `id` (number): The unique identifier of the guide.
- `name` (string): The name of the guide.
- `bio` (string): The biography of the guide.
- `avatar` (string): The URL of the guide's avatar image.
- `likes` (number): The number of likes the guide has received.
- `email` (string): The email address of the guide.
- `liked` (boolean): Indicates if the current user has liked the guide.
- `is_popular` (boolean): Indicates if the guide is popular.

### Response JSON Schema
```json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "id": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "name": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "bio": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "avatar": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "likes": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "email": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "liked": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "is_popular": {
            "type": "boolean"
        }
    }
}
```

### POST /services/activities/listings/

This endpoint is used to create a new activity listing.

#### Request Body

- `name` (text):

- `description` (text, nullable):

- `refund_rate` (text): Should be a number between 0 and 100.

- `allow_points` (text): Indicates whether or not points are allowed.

- `photos[]`(array): Photos is an array of photo objects where at least two photos are required.

    - image (img file)

- `site_id`

- `opens_at`

- `website` (text, nullable):

- `work_hours` (text): Hours in float format, can't exceed 23.99 hours and can't result in a closing time smaller than opening time (looping).


